diff:1620435735:1620409357:=52,64c52%0a%3c #foxbegin 210508-010215-221090#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Erzyan Music %0a%3c -> - NickG%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c https://youtu.be/eosqcOfjnec%0a%3c The above video is of someone singing an Erzyan song. The clothing worn by the singer in the first video is traditional clothing worn by Morodovian women dating back to the 18th century. %0a%3c %0a%3c https://youtu.be/kvHYusiQbLg%0a%3c This video is from the folk group "Merema," an Erzyan word meaning "a story, a legend," where this performance won them the "Best Authentic Band" award at the 2017 Russian World Music Awards. Since music is a powerful way of spreading a culture and a language, both of these musical groups contribute greatly to the revitalization of the Erzyan language in modern-day Russia. I think that the fact that a group like Merema can be recognized for their talent while singing a song in an endangered language shows that the Erzyan language, and Mordvinic languages in general, still have a strong community surrounding them.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210508-010215-221090#%0a---%0a> %0a
